<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 5 (1,800 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Trampling Charge.</em></strong> If the triceratops moves at least 20 ft. straight toward a creature and then hits it with a gore attack on the same turn, that target must succeed on a DC 13 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. If the target is prone, the triceratops can make one stomp attack against it as a bonus action.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Gore.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +9 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 24 (4d8 + 6) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Stomp.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +9 to hit, reach 5 ft., one prone creature. Hit: 22 (3d10 + 6) bludgeoning damage</p>

